des:
Control your aquarium with Alexa. You can turn on or off your aquarium products, you can initiate scenes. For lights, you can also ask Alexa to change the color of your lights.
To use Alexa to control your Vita devices:
1) Install the Aquatic Vita app, 
2) Create an account or login into your existing account,
3) If you have not already added your devices to the Vita app, add devices to your vita app and change the names according to your set-up (e.g. Living Room Aquarium Background Light)
4) Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market then configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
5) Search “Aquatic Vita” skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
6) Enable “Aquatic Vita” skill, and you'll be navigated to “Aquatic Vita” login page;
7) Follow the instructions on the page to complete linking;
8) Now all setup is finished. You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on the aquarium light.”
“Alexa, turn off the aquarium light.”
"Alexa, set aquarium light to blue."
